Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_cppr_threshold_ps(25.10)                timing_cppr_threshold_ps(25.10)

Name
       timing_cppr_threshold_ps

Syntax
       timing_cppr_threshold_ps <float>

       Default: 20 ps

       Specifies the maximum amount of pessimism that clock path pessimism re-
       moval (CPPR) analysis is allowed to leave in the path. The unit is pico
       seconds.  Setting  this  global to a specified value means that all the
       paths might be reported without having their  pessimism  removed.  This
       global  can  be used to speed up CPPR analysis run time. The larger the
       value of the global, the faster the run time.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

